sentences: Connie Crothers (May 2, 1941 – August 13, 2016) was an American jazz improviser and pianist.
After Tristano's death in November 1978, Crothers founded the Lennie Jazz Foundation and recorded a memorial concert album in his honor.
In 1982 she recorded an album with drummer Max Roach for New Artists Records, a label she and Roach founded.
Crothers died of lung cancer in Manhattan on August 13, 2016.
The Way I Am, Linda Satin
